@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@alexToken = course-alex-local-token
@rileyToken = course-riley-local-token

### Riley has no data-sync scope. Source and vector state must remain unchanged (403).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles
Authorization: Bearer {{rileyToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "article-riley-forbidden",
  "title": "Forbidden sync",
  "body": "This source row must not be created.",
  "category": "security"
}

### Create application source truth and derived evidence through the trusted boundary.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "article-live-sync",
  "title": "Enroll a passkey",
  "body": "Register a passkey in Security Settings before removing the password.",
  "category": "authentication"
}

### Update the same stable source/evidence identity.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles/article-live-sync
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Replace a password with a security key",
  "body": "Register the hardware security key, verify it, then revoke the previous login method."
}

### The response must contain the updated text, not the prior passkey projection.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/search?q=How%20do%20I%20revoke%20the%20previous%20security%20key%20login%3F
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### Three operations exceed the configured framework batch limit of two (400/BATCH_TOO_LARGE).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/sync/reconcile
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "articleIds": [
    "article-account-lockout",
    "article-two-factor",
    "article-api-key"
  ]
}

### Remove derived evidence and application source state.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles/article-live-sync
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### The raw framework DTO endpoint is never a public identity boundary (401/403; it may be absent as 404).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/internal/ai-data-sync/upsert
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vectorSpace": "unknown-space",
  "id": "forged",
  "content": "forged",
  "trace": {
    "authContext": {
      "subjectId": "customer-alex"
    }
  }
}
